2500|$|Law {{enforcement}} in the United States {{is one of}} three major components <b>of</b> <b>the</b> <b>criminal</b> <b>justice</b> <b>system</b> of the United States, along with courts and corrections. Although each component operates semi-independently, the three collectively form a chain leading from investigation of suspected criminal activity to administration of criminal punishment. Also, courts are vested with the power to make legal determinations regarding the conduct of the other two components.|$|E
